This Decree shall continue to be effective and binding upon the Parties and Intervenors as follows: The Decree shall continue to be effective and binding upon the Parties and Intervenors for a period of no more than ten (10) years immediately following the Effective Date, except as set forth below:
A. The obligations in Sections XII (Allocation of Hours) and XIV(A) (Movement into Grocery and Produce Apprentice) of this Decree shall terminate five (5) years after the Effective Date.
B. The obligations in Section XI (Initial Assignments) of this Decree shall terminate six (6) years after the Effective Date.
C. The obligations set forth in Section XIII (Movement to Full-Time) and Sections XIV(B) and XIV(C) with respect to ELMT and movement to all Covered Positions, except Store Manager and Assistant Store Manager, shall terminate no more than seven (7) years after the Effective Date. The obligations for movement to Store Manager and Assistant Store Manager shall terminate no more than ten (10) years after the Effective Date. The obligations in Section XIV(B) and XIV(C) may terminate earlier than seven (7) or ten (10) years, as applicable, as follows:
1. For all Covered Positions except Head Clerk (Fourth Person), the obligations in Section XTV(C) shall terminate, separately by Covered Position, on the date that the female incumbency in the Covered Position has for a period of six (6) months equaled the female incumbency in the feeder position for such Covered Position. For purposes of this subsection, the feeder position for each Covered Position shall be as follows: 
a. for Store Manager, the feeder position shall be Assistant Store  Manager;
b. for Assistant Store Manager, the feeder position shall be Head Clerk (Third Person);
c. for Senior Produce Clerk, the feeder position shall be Produce Journey Clerk;
d. for Head Clerk (Third Person), the feeder position shall be Head Clerk (Fourth Person);
e. for all other Head Clerk Covered Positions, except Head Clerk (Fourth Person), the feeder position shall be Grocery Journey Clerk (Full-Time, Part-Time, Day, and Night).
2. The obligations of Section XIV(C) with respect to Head Clerk (Fourth Person) and Section XTV(B) with respect to ELMT shall terminate on the date that the obligations in Section XIV(C) with respect to Head Clerk (Third Person) terminate. The Parties and Intervenors shall not have the right to seek to modify the Decree to extend its duration beyond the periods specified in this Section VII, except as a remedy to enforce its terms. Nothing in this Section VII, however, shall bar Class Counsel from moving after the expiration of this Decree to enforce obligations that pertain to a final Decree Year.  (Pages, 8-9)

